explanation: The solution checks if the concatenation of str1 and str2 is equal to the concatenation of str2 and str1. If not, it returns an empty string. Otherwise, it calculates the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the lengths of str1 and str2 and returns the substring of str1 with the length of the GCD. This approach takes advantage of the mathematical property that the GCD of two numbers represents the length of the largest string that can divide both strings.

